---
import PageLayout from "../../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import DefinitionTooltip from "../../components/ui/DefinitionTooltip.tsx";
import { getThemeFromURL } from "../../lib/utils";

const pageTitle = "S.R.T.P. - Sinthome Revolutionary Theoretical Practice";
const theme = getThemeFromURL(Astro.url);
---

<PageLayout title={pageTitle} useContentLayout={true} theme={theme}>
  <!-- Enhanced Title Structure -->
  <div class="text-center mb-12">
    <h1 class="text-6xl font-bold mb-4 tracking-wider" style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">S.R.T.P.</h1>
    <h2 class="text-2xl text-red-400 font-medium tracking-wide">Sinthome Revolutionary Theoretical Practice</h2>
    <div class="w-32 h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-600 to-red-800 mx-auto mt-6"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Vision Statement -->
  <div class="text-center mb-16 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--theme-text-secondary);">
        In our weekly lectures and community activities, every member is encouraged to take part in the collective study of leftist and critical theories.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed font-serif italic" style="color: var(--theme-text-secondary);">
        在每周讲座和社区活动，我们邀请每位社区成员加入左翼和批判理论的集体学习。
      </p>
      <p class="text-xl text-red-400 font-bold tracking-wide mt-6">
        逼问实践，直至它吐露未来。
      </p>
      <p class="text-xl text-red-400 font-medium tracking-wide italic">
        Interrogating <DefinitionTooltip term="praxis" client:load />, until it unveils the future.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-16 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Philosophy Section with Marx Quote -->
    <section>
      <div class="relative">
        <!-- Background glow effect -->
        <div class="absolute -inset-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-900/20 via-red-800/10 to-red-900/20 rounded-xl blur opacity-50"></div>

        <!-- Main card -->
        <div class="relative rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-md" style="background-color: var(--theme-bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--theme-border);">
          <!-- Marx Quote with special styling -->
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-red-900/20 via-red-800/10 to-transparent rounded-md p-6 border-l-4 border-red-600/60 mb-8">
            <div class="relative">
              <!-- Opening quote -->
              <div class="absolute -left-1 -top-1 text-red-600/30 text-2xl font-serif">"</div>

              <p class="italic pl-4 text-lg" style="color: var(--theme-text-secondary);">
                Die Philosophen haben die Welt nur verschieden <DefinitionTooltip term="interpretiert" client:load />; es kommt <DefinitionTooltip term="aber" client:load /> darauf an, sie zu <DefinitionTooltip term="verändern" client:load />.
              </p>

              <!-- Closing quote -->
              <div class="absolute -right-1 -bottom-1 text-red-600/30 text-2xl font-serif">"</div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-red-300 font-semibold text-sm mt-3 text-right">—— Karl Marx</p>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-6 leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--theme-text-secondary);">
            <p>
              There is no clear path that leads <DefinitionTooltip term="theoretical critique" client:load /> to social <DefinitionTooltip term="praxis" client:load />. Born from this rupture between theory and praxis,
              <DefinitionTooltip term="sinthome" client:load /> Revolutionary Theoretical Practice (<DefinitionTooltip term="srtp" client:load />) is such a special yet indispensable program that formulates the guidelines for Sinthome's social praxis.
            </p>

            <p>
              By hosting weekly lectures and seminars, <DefinitionTooltip term="srtp" client:load /> harbors a self-reflexive intellectual community that facilitates the necessary circulation between <DefinitionTooltip term="theoretical critique" client:load /> and social <DefinitionTooltip term="praxis" client:load />.
              Departing from knowledge learning and theoretical critique, we interrogate every possible dimension of our own praxis: What is the meaning of our praxis? How can it be theorized? How can it lead to new <DefinitionTooltip term="revolutionary thinking" client:load />?
            </p>

            <p>
              Yet, who is changing the world? Which world needs to be changed? On this point, Marx remained silent.
              It is precisely this silence that constitutes our origin (<DefinitionTooltip term="arche" client:load />) of departure.
            </p>

            <p>
              The task of <DefinitionTooltip term="srtp" client:load /> is established within this call. We are not here to interpret the world in order to understand it,
              nor do we interpret first and only "then (<DefinitionTooltip term="dann" client:load />)" go on to change it. Marx's "<DefinitionTooltip term="aber" client:load />" precedes all interpretation,
              precedes all theory. Changing the world is the sole a priori, the absolute principle.
            </p>

            <p class="text-lg text-red-300 font-semibold">
              <DefinitionTooltip term="srtp" client:load /> is both a machine of reflection and an apparatus of interrogation:
              Its very existence is a reminder—The world must be changed, and all theory and <DefinitionTooltip term="praxis" client:load /> must assume this mission.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Activities Section -->
    <section>
      <div class="relative">
        <!-- Background glow effect -->
        <div class="absolute -inset-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-900/20 via-red-800/10 to-red-900/20 rounded-xl blur opacity-50"></div>

        <!-- Main card -->
        <div class="relative rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-md" style="background-color: var(--theme-bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--theme-border);">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6" style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">Activities</h3>

          <div class="space-y-6 leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--theme-text-secondary);">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-red-300 mb-3">Lectures & Seminars in Boston</h4>
              <p class="mb-2">
                <strong style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">Every Saturday from 3–5 pm</strong> (EST, starting September 2025)
              </p>
              <p class="mb-2">
                <strong style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">Location:</strong> Boston University, Stone Science Building, Room 116
              </p>
              <p class="mb-4">
                Our weekly lectures and seminars provide a space for collective study and critical engagement with leftist theory, philosophy, and contemporary social issues. Each session combines theoretical exploration with practical applications, fostering dialogue between academic knowledge and lived experience.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-red-300 mb-3">Online Community Platform</h4>
              <p class="mb-2">
                <strong style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">Format:</strong> WeChat groups + Tencent Meeting for lectures
              </p>
              <p class="mb-2">
                <strong style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">Schedule:</strong> Regular online discussions and virtual lecture attendance
              </p>
              <p class="mb-4">
                For those unable to attend in-person sessions, our online platform provides access to live-streamed lectures, discussion forums, and study groups. This digital community extends our reach globally while maintaining the intimate, collaborative spirit of our local gatherings.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-red-300 mb-3">Summer Intensive Series</h4>
              <p class="mb-2">
                <strong style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">Summer 2025:</strong> Four specialized lecture series (8 weeks each)
              </p>
              <p class="mb-2">
                <strong style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">Topics:</strong> History, Community Practice, Political Philosophy, and Lacan's Seminar on Love
              </p>
              <p class="mb-4">
                Our intensive summer programs dive deep into specific theoretical frameworks and their practical applications. These extended series allow for comprehensive exploration of complex topics while building sustained intellectual community among participants.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-8 p-6 rounded-lg" style="background-color: var(--theme-bg-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--theme-border);">
              <p class="font-medium mb-2" style="color: var(--theme-text-secondary);">Join Our Learning Community</p>
              <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--theme-text-muted);">
                All activities are open to community members interested in critical theory and social practice.
                No prior academic background required—just curiosity and commitment to collective learning.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Call to Action -->
    <section class="mt-16 text-center p-12 rounded-lg" style="background-color: var(--theme-bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--theme-border);">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--theme-text-primary);">Join the Critical Inquiry</h3>
        <p class="text-lg mb-8" style="color: var(--theme-text-secondary);">
          Be part of the intellectual community that bridges theory and praxis in revolutionary thinking.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
        <a
          href="/what-we-do/public-lectures"
          class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 bg-red-600 hover:bg-red-700 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition-all duration-300 transform hover:scale-105 shadow-lg hover:shadow-red-600/25"
        >
          View Our Lectures
          <span class="ml-2">→</span>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 font-semibold rounded-lg transition-all duration-300"
          style="background-color: transparent; border: 1px solid var(--theme-border); color: var(--theme-text-secondary);"
        >
          Get Involved
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</PageLayout>